properties.title: IGDA Summit
properties.description:
When: Mon Jul 18, 2011 to Tue Jul 19, 2011 
Where: Fairmont Olympic Hotel 411, University Street Seattle, WA 98101
Event Status: confirmed
Event Description: The IGDA Summit is about Developers helping Developers. It is a home for our development community that provides valuable professional development, actionable insight and candid discussion to elevate our craft. For this inaugural IGDA Summit, industry leaders from many disciplines have come together to produce a program with content to serve line developers, entrepreneurial developers, qa developers, freelancers, team leaders, project managers, business development executives, investors, studio directors, and all others seeking to learn from and share techniques for creating successful careers, games and businesses.

The IGDA Summit will cover topics including: Entrepreneurship, Game Development Community, Quality Assurance, User Testing, Monetization, Indie Boot Camp, Writing about Games, Writing in Games, Quality of Life and Legal Insights. This is also an opportunity for our community to give back to our global community. We are proud that the IGDA Foundation will be holding a charity dinner on Monday evening, July 19th to support our new IGDA Foundation Japan Scholars initiative, Eric Dysband Memorial Scholarships and other game developer centric efforts in 2011.
